0Australia%20chased%20down%20the%20target%20of%20241%20runs%20in%20the%20final%20with%20ease.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAustralia's%20Travis%20Head%20took%20a%20spectacular%20diving%20catch%20on%20the%20bowling%20of%20Maxwell%20to%20send%20Rohit%20back%20in%20the%20dressing%20room.%20Head%20also%20turned%20the%20match-winner%20for%20Australia%2C%20becoming%20only%20the%20third%20Australian%20player%20to%20score%20a%20century%20in%20an%20ODI%20World%20Cup%20final.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20playing%20a%20match-winning%20knock%20of%20137%20runs%2C%20it%20was%20never%20in%20doubt%20that%20Australia%20opener%20Travis%20Head%20would%20be%20named%20Player%20of%20the%20Match%20after%20a%20standout%20display%20that%20earned%20Australia's%20men%20their%20sixth%20Cricket%20World%20Cup%20title.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20taking%20Australia%20to%20its%20sixth%20World%20Cup%20title%20victory%2C%20centurion%20Head%20expressed%20his%20astonishment%2C%20stating%20that%20he%20%26quot%3Bnever%20expected%20this%20in%20a%20million%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAustralia%20opener%20dominated%20the%20Indian%20bowlers%20on%20his%20way%20to%20a%20match-winning%20knock%20of%20137%20in%20120%20balls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNever%20expected%20this%2C%20not%20in%20a%20million%20years%2C%20truly%20an%20exceptional%20day.%20Lot%20better%20than%20sitting%20on%20the%20couch%20at%20home.%20Really%20glad%20to%20contribute%2C%20the%20first%20twenty%20balls%20I%20played%20gave%20me%20a%20lot%20of%20confidence%20and%20yea%20I%20was%20able%20to%20carry%20through.%20The%20way%20Mitch%20Marsh%20came%20out%20and%20took%20the%20game%20on%2C%20he%20set%20the%20tone.%20That%20was%20the%20energy%20we%20wanted%20and%20we%20knew%20the%20wicket%20may%20get%20tough.%20It%20was%20a%20great%20decision%20to%20bowl%20first%20after%20winning%20the%20toss.%20I%20felt%20the%20wicket%20got%20better%20as%20the%20day%20went%20on.%20It%20took%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20spin%2C%20it%20paid%20dividends.%