s%2C%20Delta%20Air%20Lines%2C%20and%20United%20Airlines%2C%20are%20not%20thrilled%20with%20the%20prospect%20of%20such%20a%20change%2C%20which%20consumers%20have%20advocated%20for%20in%20numerous%20letters%20submitted%20to%20the%20Department%20of%20Transportation%20(DOT).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoug%20Mullen%2C%20the%20deputy%20general%20counsel%20at%20the%20lobbying%20group%20Airlines%20for%20America%2C%20said%20at%20a%20hearing%20earlier%20this%20year%20that%20such%20a%20change%20would%20create%20%26quot%3Bconfusion%20and%20frustration%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20he%20remarked%20that%20the%20DOT%20%26quot%3Bshould%20not%20regulate%20in%20this%20area.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAirlines%20for%20America%20lobbies%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20three%20aforementioned%20US%20air%20carriers%2C%20which%20transport%20millions%20of%20fliers%20domestically%20and%20internationally%20each%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20DOT%2C%20the%20airline%20industry%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bts.gov%2Ftopics%2Fairlines-and-airports%2Fbaggage-fees-airline-2022%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etook%20in%3C%2Fa%3E%20nearly%20%246.8%20billion%20in%20baggage%20fees%20in%202022.%20American%20Airlines%20collected%20almost%20%241.4%20billion%20in%20baggage%20fees%2C%20the%20domestic%20industry%20leader%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPer%20The%20Post%2C%20the%20DOT%20has%20sought%20to%20create%20guidelines%20regarding%20how%20airlines%20should%20issue%20refunds%2C%20as%20well%20as%20rules%20for%20adding%20checked%20bag%20fees%20and%20tacking%20on%20change%20fees.%20But%20airlines%20have%20been%20critical%20of%20the%20efforts%2C%20with%20carriers%20stating%20that%20the%20department's%20proposals%20may%20be%20impractical.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegarding%20concert%20fees%2C%20another%20sore%20spot%20for%20consumers%2C%20Live%20Nation%20executive%20vice%20president%20for%20corporate%20and%20regulatory%20affairs%20Dan%20Wall%20told%20The%20Post%20that%20the%20company%20cannot%20create%20mandates%20for%20venues%20that%20it%20doesn't%20own.%20But%20he%20said%20that%20federal%20regulations%20on%20company%20disclosures%20would%20make%20certain%20that%20%26quot%3Beverybody%20does%20it%20so%20that%20nobody%20is%20disadvantaged%20for%20doing%20the%20right%20thing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhidden-junk-fees-companies-biden-crackdown-lobbyists-fighting-rules-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700444127000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655aaedd22cf74a57399e89b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhidden-junk-fees-companies-biden-crackdown-lobbyists-fighting-rules-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Washington%20Post%20analyzed%20federal%20lobbying%20files%20as%20the%20administration%20works%20to%20save%20consumers%20from%20collectively%20paying%20billions%20in%20fees%20each%20year.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(John%20L.%20Dorman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhidden-junk-fees-companies-biden-crackdown-lobbyists-fighting-rules-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Infosys%20to%20give%2080%25%20variable%20pay%2C%20here's%20HR's%20email%20to%20employees%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700444020000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105340617%2Cimgsize-27962.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fgadgets-news%2Finfosys-to-give-80-variable-pay-heres-hrs-email-to-employees%2Farticleshow%2F105340625.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Infosys%20will%20be%20giving%20a%20quarterly%20performance%20bonus%20to%20eligible%20employees%20with%20an%20average%20payout%20of%2080%25.%20The%20bonus%20will%20be%20given%20to%20employees%20at%20position%20level%206%20and%20be