hor%22%3A%22TIMESOFINDIA.COM%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fgadgets-news%2Fedtech-unicorn-physicswallah-cuts-over-100-jobs-read-companys-statement%2Farticleshow%2F105340612.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Is%20There%20Life%20After%20Electoral%20Bonds%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F16115416%2Frupee-g803a66102_1920.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20introduced%20in%202017%2C%20Electoral%20Bonds%20(EBs)%20seem%20to%20have%20become%20a%20popular%20topic%20in%20the%20national%20discourse%20ever%20since%20the%20recent%20three-day%20hearing%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20(SC).%20There%20has%20been%20fair%20bit%20of%20writing%20in%20the%20print%20and%20digital%20media%2C%20and%20also%20some%20discussion%20on%20TV.%20In%20quite%20a%20few%20of%20media%20writings%20suggestions%20have%20been%20given%20on%20how%20to%20make%20EBs%20less%20opaque%20or%20confidential%20(as%20the%20Solicitor%20General%20of%20India%20kept%20insisting%20during%20the%20SC%20hearings).%20Quite%20a%20few%20correspondents%2Freporters%20have%20also%20asked%20me%20to%20specifically%20comment%20on%20how%20to%20make%20EBs%20%E2%80%9Cacceptable%E2%80%9D.%20That%20is%20what%20prompts%20the%20title%20of%20this%20piece.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20us%20seem%20to%20have%20forgotten%20that%20political%20parties%2C%20elections%20and%20democracy%20existed%20even%20before%202017%2C%20i.e.%2C%20before%20the%20introduction%20of%20EBs.%20Existence%20of%20political%20parties%20implies%20that%20parties%20got%20money%20to%20conduct%20their%20affairs%20including%20contesting%20elections%2C%20and%20there%20was%20no%20mystery%20where%20and%20how%20they%20got%20the%20money%20and%20from%20whom.%20There%20were%20several%20methods%20of%20political%20parties%20getting%20money%20such%20as%20(a)%20by%20cheque%2C%20(b)%20by%20bank%20draft%2C%20(c)%20by%20digital%20transfer%20through%20banks%2C%20(d)%20digital%20payment%20through%20apps%2C%20(e)%20Electoral%20Trusts%2C%20and%20(f)%20cash%2C%20with%20each%20donation%20being%20not%20more%20than%20Rs%202%2C000.%20The%20most%20popular%20method%2C%20of%20course%2C%20was%20cash%20in%20unlimited%20amounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22How%20Two%20IAS%20Officers%20Chaperoned%20the%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Bill%20Despite%20RBI's%20Objections%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fhow-two-ias-officers-chaperoned-the-electoral-bonds-bill-despite-rbis-objections%5C%22%3EHow%20Two%20IAS%20Officers%20Chaperoned%20the%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Bill%20Despite%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20Objections%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20complication%20was%2C%20and%20still%20is%2C%20that%20there%20was%20no%20incontrovertible%20proof%20of%20the%20transactions%20by%20the%20last%2C%20and%20the%20most%20common%2C%20method%20and%20therefore%20no%20one%20except%20the%20giver%20and%20the%20receiver%20knew%20how%20much%20money%20was%20given%20by%20whom%20and%20to%20whom.%20Some%20insiders%20and%20snoopers%20were%20of%20course%2C%20the%20expected%20exceptions.%20Consequently%2C%20it%20was%20not%20possible%20for%20people%20at%20large%20to%20know%20whether%20decisions%20by%20a%20particular%20political%20party%20in%20power%2C%20in%20the%20Centre%20of%20any%20of%20the%20States%2C%20were%20motivated%20by%20welfare%20of%20the%20people%20at%20large%20or%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20a%20donor%20of%20a%20large%20amount%20of%20unaccounted%20cash.%20We%20also%20need%20to%20remember%20that%20donations%20need%20not%20be%20strictly%20only%20in%20cash%2C%20they%20can%20also%20be%20in%20kind%20such%20as%20making%20aircraft%20or%20helicopters%20booked%20in%20the%20name%20of%20some%20company%20or%20individual%2C%20being%20provided%20to%20a%20political%20party%20for%20its%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20Union%20of%20India%20has%20claimed%20during%20the%20hearings%20in%20the%20SC%20that%20ever%20since%20EBs%20were%20introduced%20that%20transparency%20of%20electoral%20funding%20has%20improved%2C%20the%20statement%20made%20above%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9Cno%20one%20except%20the%20giver%20and%20the%20receiver%20knew%20how%20much%20money%20was%20given%20by%20whom%20and%20to%20whom%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20is%20still%20valid%20with%20a%20very%20interesting%20change.%20Going%20strictly%20according%20to%20the%20EBs%20scheme%20as%20announced%20by%20the%20government%2C%20not%20even%20the%20receiver%20may%20know%20who%20has%20given%20the%20money!%20This%20of%20course%20is%20creative%20imagination%20of%20the%20highest%20order%20as%20everyone%20knows%20that%20one%20who%20gives%20money%20always%20makes%20sure%20the%20receiver%20knows%20who%20is%20the%20giver.%20The%20pious%20concept%20of%20%3Cem%3Egupt-daan%3C%2Fem%3E%20(anonymous%20donation)%20does%20not%20apply%20to%20political%20donations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20can%2C%20and%20should%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20do%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20will%20refrain%20from%20suggesting%20what%20the%20SC%20%3Cem%3Eshould%3C%2Fem%3E%20do%20because%20the%20judgment%20is%20reserved%2C%20but%20being%20part%20of%20one%20of%20the%20petitioner-organisations%2C%20what%20we%20have%20requested%20the%20SC%20to%20do%20is%20to%20declare%20Sections%20135%2C%20137%2C%2011%20and%20154%20of%20the%20Finance%20Act%202017%20and%20consequential%20amendments%20in%20Section%2031%20of%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%201934%2C%20Section%2029C%20of%20the%20Representation%20of%20the%20People%20Act%201951%2C%20Section%2013A%20of%20the%20Income%20Tax%20Act%201961%2C%20and%20Section%20182%20of%20the%20Companies%20Act%202013%3B%20and%20Section%20236%20of%20Finance%20Act%202016%20and%20consequential%20amendments%20in%20Section%202(1)(j)(vi)%20of%20the%20Foreign%20Contribution%20(Regulation)%20Act%202010%20%E2%80%9Cas%20being%20unconstitutional%2C%20null%20and%20void%E2%80%9D.%20What%20this%20legal%20jargon%20means%20is%20that%2C%20in%20effect%2C%20we%20have%20requested%20the%20SC%20to%20declare%20the%20Electoral%20Bonds%20scheme%20as%20unconstitutional%20or%20illegal%2C%20or%20in%20even%20simpler%20words%20to%20strike%20it%20down.%20And%20of%20course%2C%20this%20is%20what%20we%20would%20like%20the%20SC%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20issue%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20%3Cem%3Ecan%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20SC%20do%3F%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20is%2C%20I%20think%2C%20more%20important%20and%20needs%20some%20comment.%20A%20lot%20of%20commentary%20has%20suggested%20that%20the%20SC%20should%20make%20some%20modifications%20in%20the%20EBs%20scheme%20to%20remove%20what%20has%20been%20variously%20called%20as%20%E2%80%9Cselective%20disclosure%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%9Cselective%20or%20partial%20transparency%E2%80%9D%20and%20of%20course%20the%20celebrated%20%E2%80%9Cpartial%20confidentiality%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20necessary%20to%20go%20to%20some%20basics%20in%20order%20to%20resolve%20this%20issue%20of%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20%3Cem%3Ecan%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20SC%20do%3F%E2%80%9D.%20Under%20the%20principle%20of%20separation%20of%20powers%2C%20the%20three%20pillars%20of%20the%20State%20%E2%80%93%20the%20legislature%2C%20the%20executive%20and%20the%20judiciary%20%E2%80%93%20have%20separate%20and%20distinct%20powers.%20In%20simple%20terms%2C%20the%20prime%20function%20of%20the%20legislature%20is%20to%20%3Cem%3Emake%3C%2Fem%3E%20laws%2C%20the%20prime%20function%20of%20the%20executive%20is%20to%20%3Cem%3Eimplement%3C%2Fem%3E%20laws%2C%20and%20the%20prime%20function%20of%20the%20judiciary%20is%20to%20%3Cem%3Einterpret%3C%2Fem%3E%20laws.%20The%20power%20to%20interpret%20laws%20implies%20and%20includes%20the%20power%20of%20%3Cem%3Ejudicial%20review%3C%2Fem%3E.%20This%20power%20of%20judicial%20review%20implies%20that%20the%20higher%20judiciary%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20the%20high%20courts%20have%20the%20power%20to%20review%20any%20action%20of%20the%20legislature%20and%20the%20executive%20and%20decide%20whether%20these%20actions%20are%20in%20keeping%20with%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%20or%20not%2C%20and%20if%20they%20find%20any%20of%20the%20actions%20not%20to%20be%20in%20line%20with%20the%20Constitution%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20the%20high%20courts%20have%20the%20power%20to%20declare%20any%20such%20action%20as%20unconstitutional.%20That%20is%20why%20in%20our%20petition%20we%20have%20requested%20the%20SC%20to%20declare%20the%20above-mentioned%20laws%20as%20%E2%80%9Cunconstitutional%2C%20null%20and%20void%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Time%20to%20Shut%20the%20Floodgates%20of%20Secret%20Political%20Party%20Funding%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Ftime-to-shut-the-floodgates-of-secret-political-party-funding%5C%22%3ETime%20to%20Shut%20the%20Floodgates%20of%20Secret%20Political%20Party%20Funding%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20maintain%20that%20all%20that%20the%20SC%20%3Cem%3Ecan%3C%2Fem%3E%20do%20is%20to%20declare%20these%20laws%20as%20unconstitutional%20and%20no%20more.%20While%20many%20of%20the%20suggestions%20that%20have%20been%2C%20and%20are%20still%20being%20made%2C%20about%20what%20the%20SC%20should%20do%2C%20are%20valuable%20but%20they%20are%20all%20outside%20the%20remit%20of%20the%20SC.%20What%20must%20be%20remembered%20is%20that%20laws%20can%20be%20made%20only%20by%20the%20legislature.%20Yes%2C%20the%20SC%20can%20certainly%20make%20suggestions%2C%20%3Cem%3Eif%3C%2Fem%3E%20it%20wishes%20to%20do%20that%2C%20but%20it%20cannot%2C%20in%20my%20view%2C%20make%20modifications%20to%20the%20scheme%20as%20enunciated%20by%20the%20government%20and%20passed%20by%20the%20Parliament.%20As%20an%20aside%2C%20the%20passing%20of%20the%20EBs%20scheme%20by%20the%20Parliament%20is%20also%20in%20doubt%20because%20it%20was%20included%20in%20a%20Money%20Bill%2C%20thus%20disabling%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20from%20making%20changes%20to%20it%20but%20that%20issue%20is%20being%20examined%20by%20a%20separate%20constitutional%20bench%20of%20seven%20judges%20and%20was%20therefore%20not%20argued%20before%20the%20current%20bench%20of%20five%20judges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20we%20just%20have%20to%20wait%20and%20see%20what%20the%20SC%20does.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EJagdeep%20S.%20Chhokar%20is%20a%20concerned%20citizen.%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20name%3D%5C%22_edn2%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fis-there-life-after-electoral-bonds%23_ednref2%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700443834000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F16115416%2Frupee-g803a66102_1920.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fis-there-life-after-electoral-bonds%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20lot%20of%20us%20seem%20to%20have%20forgotten%20that%20political%20parties%2C%20elections%20and%20democracy%20existed%20even%20before%202017%20%E2%80%93%20and%20so%20before%20the%20existence%20of%20electoral%20bonds.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fis-there-life-after-electoral-bonds%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Amitabh%20Bachchan%20Retrospective%20Set%20at%20France%E2%80%99s%203%20Continents%20Festival%20(EXCLUSIVE)%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700443800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2FDeewar1-Amitabh-Bachchan.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235799893%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20nine-film%20retrospective%20of%20Indian%20cinema%20acting%20legend%20Amitabh%20Bachchan%20is%20set%20for%20the%20Festival%20des%203%20Continents%20in%20Nantes%2C%20France.%20The%20retrospective%2C%20titled%20%E2%80%9CAmitabh%20Bachchan%2C%20Big%20B%20Forever%