suing%20commercial%20success%20(a%20likely%20choice!)%2C%20Altman%20would%20also%20have%20no%20trouble%20poaching%20the%20brightest%20minds%20from%20OpenAI.%20His%20cofounder%2C%20Greg%20Brockman%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-president-greg-brockman-quits-sam-altman-ceo-ousted-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimmediately%20quit%20in%20protest%20of%20Altman's%20removal%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-optimistic-ceo-sam-altman-greg-brockman-will-return-board-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edid%20three%20senior%20researchers%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20staffers%20were%20threatening%20to%20resign%20if%20Altman%20wasn't%20reinstated%2C%20the%20Verge%20reported.%20And%20Altman%20called%20to%20them%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fsama%2Fstatus%2F1726099792600903681%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewith%20a%20post%20on%20X%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20his%20appreciation%2C%20%26quot%3Bi%20love%20the%20openai%20team%20so%20much.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoes%20he%20love%20them%20enough%20to%20hire%20them%20for%20a%20new%20venture%20that%20would%20be%20swimming%20in%20venture%20cash%3F%20As%20that's%20how%20so%20many%20startups%20launch%E2%80%94%20by%20hiring%20people%20from%20the%20last%20company%20%E2%80%94%20I'm%20going%20to%20say%20yes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20which%20means%20that%20the%20biggest%20loser%20if%20Altman%20can't%20be%20convinced%20to%20return%20isn't%20Altman.%20And%20it%20isn't%20OpenAI%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20Microsoft%20and%20CEO%20Satya%20Nadella.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOpenAI%20is%20like%20Mahomes%20to%20the%20Chiefs.%20Nadella%20recognizes%20this%20and%20losing%20Sam%20is%20not%20an%20option.%20This%20OpenAI%20board%20is%20way%20over%20its%20head%20and%20the%20failed%20coup%20is%20now%20backfiring%2C%26quot%3B%20investor%20Dan%20Ives%2C%20an%20analyst%20at%20Webush%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft%20has%20invested%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-01-23%2Fmicrosoft-makes-multibillion-dollar-investment-in-openai%23xj4y7vzkg%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20reported%20%2410%2B%20billion%20dollars%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20owns%20a%20sizeable%20stake%20%E2%80%94%20some%20reports%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.barrons.com%2Farticles%2Fmicrosoft-stock-openai-chatgpt-stake-value-ai-5de2525c%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esay%20as%20much%20as%2049%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20in%20a%20for-profit%20unit%20run%20by%20the%20non-profit%20OpenAI.%20(Although%20Microsoft%20has%20never%20publicly%20confirmed%20the%20size%20of%20that%20stake.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20OpenAI%20non-profit%20was%20run%20by%20a%20six-person%20governing%20board%20who%20owned%20no%20equity%20and%20included%20Altman%20and%20Brockman.%20So%20a%20simple%20majority%20vote%20was%20all%20it%20took%20to%20fire%20Altman%20and%20install%20CTO%20Mira%20Murati%20as%20interim%20CEO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20only%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-microsoft-employees-shocked-at-altmans-ouster-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egave%20Microsoft%20a%20few%20minutes%20advance%20warning%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20announcing%20Altman's%20ouster%2C%20sources%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20The%20company%20has%2C%20publicly%20at%20least%2C%20stood%20by%20the%20board's%20decision.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20a%20long-term%20agreement%20with%20OpenAI%20with%20full%20access%20to%20everything%20we%20need%20to%20deliver%20on%20our%20innovation%20agenda%20and%20an%20exciting%20product%20roadmap%3B%20and%20remain%20committed%20to%20our%20partnership%2C%20and%20to%20Mira%20and%20the%20team%2C%26quot%3B%20Microsoft%20CEO%20Satya%20Nadella%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUntil%20Friday%2C%20Microsoft's%20deal%20with%20OpenAI%20was%20a%20major%20coup%20for%20Nadella%2C%20giving%20Microsoft%20deep%20access%20to%20the%20technology%20at%20the%20center%20of%20AI%2C%20while%20preventing%20its%20competitors%20from%20doing%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20should%20Altman%20refuse%20to%20return%20and%20instead%20form%20a%20new%20AI%20startup%2C%20he%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-kicked-off-a-flood-of-emoji-posts-from-openai-executives-what-do-they-mean-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecertainly%20easily%20fill%20it%20with%20the%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20know%20the%20secrets%20of%20OpenAI%20technology.%20And%20he's%20also%20likely%20to%20seek%20another%20cloud%20investor%2Fpartner.%20Generative%20AI%20needs%20massive%2C%20specialized%20compute%20power%20to%20perform%2C%20especially%20to%20perform%20for%20millions%20of%20customers.%20Google%20or%20Amazon%20would%20almost%20certainly%20try%20to%20make%20Altman%20a%20deal%20he%20couldn't%20refuse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20would%20be%20much%20safer%20for%20Nadella%20to%20pressure%20OpenAI%20into%20getting%20Altman%20to%20come%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20biggest%20worry%20is%20the%20Altman%20sweepstakes%20end%20up%20in%20the%20Google%20or%20Amazon%20backyard%20which%20would%20be%20a%20nightmare%20for%20Microsoft%2C%26quot%3B%20Ives%20wrote%20in%20a%20research%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it's%20not%20just%20the%20money%20invested%2C%20and%20the%20gains%20of%20that%20investment%2C%20that%20would%20be%20lost%20for%20Microsoft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft%20has%20been%20baking%20OpenAI%20technology%20into%20pretty%20much%20all%20of%20its%20major%20products%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-thursday-night-football-ad-100-million-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebeating%20its%20rivals%20to%20market.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20month%20the%20company%20made%20over%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-microsoft-employees-shocked-at-altmans-ouster-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E100%20announcements%20of%20integrations%20with%3C%2Fa%3E%20OpenAI%20tech%20across%20Microsoft's%20AI%20tools%2C%20AI%20models%2C%20tools%20in%20its%20cloud%2C%20the%20company%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20It%20put%20Copilot%20%E2%80%94%20its%20chat%20assistant%20based%20on%20GPT%20%E2%80%94%20everywhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Microsoft%20has%20also%20been%20making%20cuts%2C%20or%20outright%20winding%20down%2C%20various%20other%20internal%20homegrown%20AI%20projects%20to%20lean%20into%20OpenAI%20tech%2C%20sources%20have%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20shut%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-shutters-project-airsim-ai-strategy-openai-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edown%20various%20%26quot%3Bindustrial%20metaverse%26quot%3B%20projects%20and%20laid%20off%20%3C%2Fa%3Estaff%2C%20as%20BI%20previously%20reported.%20That%20homegrown%20%26quot%3Bindustrial%20metaverse%26quot%3B%20had%20been%20a%20key%20AI%20strategy%20before%20ChatGPT%20took%20off%20like%20it%20did%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20that%20means%20that%20if%20OpenAI%20up%20and%20implodes%2C%20Microsoft%20no%20longer%20has%20a%20fast%20backup%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20various%20reports%20%E2%80%94%20and%20just%20plain%20common%20sense%20%E2%80%94%20say%20that%20Altman%20won't%20come%20back%20unless%20the%20management%20structure%20of%20OpenAI%20is%20altered%2C%20and%20the%20four%20board%20members%20who%20fired%20him%20resign.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShould%20that%20happen%2C%20Microsoft%20could%20actually%20wind%20up%20in%20a%20better%20position%20to%20influence%20this%20all-important%20company%20that%20seems%20to%20need%20badly%20need%20the%20guidance%2C%20probably%20with%20a%20board%20seat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20growing%20consensus%20from%20Silicon%20Valley%20and%20Wall%20Street%20is%20that%20the%20days%20for%20this%20four-person%20board%20are%20numbered%20and%20Altman%20will%20be%20back%20at%20OpenAI%20and%20ultimately%20Microsoft%20in%20an%20even%20stronger%20position%20to%20control%20OpenAI's%20strategic%20direction%2C%26quot%3B%20Ives%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faltman-openai-nightmare-microsoft-investor-says-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700429076000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655a72f39c7d23cb3b9d26ac%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faltman-openai-nightmare-microsoft-investor-says-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22If%20OpenAI%20up%20and%20implodes%2C%20Microsoft%20no%20longer%20has%20a%20fast%20AI%20tech%20backup%20plan.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jbort%40insider.com%20(Julie%20Bort)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A101%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faltman-openai-nightmare-microsoft-investor-says-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Rosalynn%20Carter%2C%20Former%20US%20First%20Lady%2C%20Humanitarian%2C%20Dies%20At%2096%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EFormer%20US%20first%20lady%20Rosalynn%20Carter%2C%20the%20wife%20of%20former%20president%20Jimmy%20Carter%2C%20died%20Sunday%20at%20age%2096%20at%20the%20couple's%20home%20in%20the%20southern%20state%20of%20Georgia%2C%20their%20nonprofit%20organization%20announced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERosalynn%20Carter%20was%20best%20known%20for%20her%20work%20post-White%20House%2C%20as%20she%20and%20her%20husband%20championed%20human%20rights%2C%20democracy%20and%20health%20issues%20around%20the%20world%20--%20all%20while%20maintaining%20a%20notably%20humble%20public%20image.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20had%20joined%20her%20husband%20in%20at-home%20hospice%20care%20on%20Friday%20after%20being%20diagnosed%20with%20dementia%20in%20May.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFormer%20first%20lady%20Rosalynn%20Carter%2C%20a%20passionate%20champion%20of%20mental%20health%2C%20caregiving%20and%20women's%20rights%2C%20passed%20away%20Sunday...%20at%20her%20home%20in%20Plains%2C%20Georgia%2C%20at%20the%20age%20of%2096%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Carter%20Center%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe%20died%20peacefully%2C%20with%20family%20by%20her%20side.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRosalynn%20was%20my%20equal%20partner%20in%20everything%20I%20ever%20accomplished%2C%26quot%3B%20Jimmy%20Carter%20said%20in%20the%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe%20gave%20me%20wise%20guidance%20and%20encouragement%20when%20I%20needed%20it.%20As%20long%20as%20Rosalynn%20was%20in%20the%20world%2C%20I%20always%20knew%20somebody%20loved%20and%20supported%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20former%20Democratic%20president%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThroughout%20Jimmy%20Carter's%20long%20political%20career%2C%20his%20wife%20was%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20his%20campaigns.%20Once%20in%20the%20White%20House%20--%20from%201977%20to%201981%20--%20Rosalynn%20Carter%20stood%20out%20as%20a%20first%20lady%20intent%20on%20being%20involved%20in%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe%20attended%20Cabinet%20meetings%20and%20major%20briefings%2C%20frequently%20represented%20the%20Chief%20Executive%20at%20ceremonial%20occasions%20and%20served%20as%20the%20president's%20personal%20emissary%20to%20Latin%20American%20countries%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20White%20House%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Sorely%20missed'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERosalynn%20Carter%20was%20born%20in%20the%20small%20town%20of%20Plains%20on%20August%2018%2C%201927%2C%20as%20the%20first%20of%20four%20children.%20At%2013%20her%20father%20died%20and%20she%20worked%20alongside%20her%20mother%2C%20who%20became%20a%20dressmaker%20to%20make%20ends%20meet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20met%20Jimmy%20Carter%20in%201945%20while%20she%20was%20in%20college%20and%20he%20was%20on%20leave%20from%20the%20US%20Naval%20Academy%20in%20Annapolis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20married%20in%201946%2C%20and%20hold%20several%20longevity%20records%20in%20US%20politics%3A%20the%20longest-wed%20presidential%20couple%20and%2C%20for%2099-year-old%20Jimmy%20Carter%2C%20the%20oldest%20living%20US%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Carter%20Center%2C%20the%20former%20first%20lady%20is%20survived%20by%20her%20four%20children%2C%2011%20grandchildren%20and%2014%20great-grandchildren%2C%20after%20losing%20a%20grandson%20in%202015.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBesides%20being%20a%20loving%20mother%20and%20extraordinary%20first%20lady%2C%20my%20mother%20was%20a%20great%20humanitarian%20in%20her%20own%20right%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Carters'%20son%20Chip%20Carter%20said%20in%20the%20Center's%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe%20will%20be%20sorely%20missed%20not%20only%20by%20our%20family%20but%20by%20the%20many%20people%20who%20have%20better%20mental%20health%20care%20and%20access%20to%20resources%20for%20caregiving%20today.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20family%20announced%20in%20February%20this%20year%20that%20Jimmy%20Carter%20had%20entered%20hospice%20care%20in%20Plains%20--%20at%20the%20same%20modest%20house%20he%20and%20Rosalynn%20have%20lived%20in%20since%20the%201960s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20one-term%20Democratic%20president%20has%20since%20surprised%20many%20by%20continuing%20to%20welcome%20visitors%2C%20receive%20news%20about%20the%20Carter%20Center's%20humanitarian%20work%2C%20and%20frequently%20enjoy%20ice%20cream%2C%20according%20to%20his%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700428740000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-11%2Ftn7tfe18_rosalynn-carter_625x300_20_November_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-n