a%20and%20Co.%20were%20bowled%20out%20for%20240%20before%20Australia%20strode%20to%20a%20six-wicket%20win%20in%20the%20ICC%20Cricket%20World%20Cup%202023%20final%20at%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20Stadium%20in%20Ahmedabad%20on%20Sunday.%20We%20take%20a%20look%20at%20the%20five%20turning%20points%20that%20led%20to%20India's%20defeat%20in%20the%20final.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EShubman%20Gill%20fails%20to%20fire%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPut%20into%20bat%20on%20a%20slow%20pitch%2C%20the%20Indian%20opener%20encountered%20difficulty%20in%20stroke-making.%20Rohit%20Sharma%20batted%20fluently%20at%20one%20end%20but%20Shubman%20Gill%20couldn't%20provide%20India%20with%20a%20strong%20start%20in%20the%20final.%20A%20solid%20opening%20start%20was%20the%20success%20formula%20of%20the%20team's%20previous%2010-match%20unbeaten%20run%20in%20the%20tournament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Australian%20bowlers%20read%20the%20conditions%20well%2C%20utilising%20slower%20deliveries%20to%20stop%20the%20Indian%20batters%20from%20playing%20their%20shots%20early%20on.%20Gill%20made%20an%20early%20exit%2C%20failing%20to%20make%20a%20significant%20impact%20on%20the%20scoring.%20Similarly%2C%20Rohit%20Sharma%20continued%20to%20take%20the%20attack%20to%20Mitchell%20Starc%20and%20Josh%20Hazlewood%20in%20the%20initial%20phase%20of%20the%20innings%20before%20he%20was%20dismissed%20by%20Glenn%20Maxwell.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESlow%20middle%20overs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20Shubman%20Gill's%20dismissal%20in%20the%20fifth%20over%2C%20Rohit%20Sharma%20continued%20to%20play%20attacking%20strokes%2C%20contributing%20a%2031-ball%2047%20before%20getting%20out%20in%20the%2010th%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20skipper's%20departure%2C%20India%20were%20in%20a%20comfortable%20position%20at%2080%2F2%20at%20that%20stage.%20However%2C%20it%20was%20in%20the%20next%2020%20overs%20that%20India%20lost%20the%20match.%20Following%20the%20dismissal%20of%20Shreyas%20Iyer%20(4)%2C%20India%20were%2081%2F3%20in%20the%2011th%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVirat%20Kohli%20and%20KL%20Rahul%20got%20down%20to%20shore%20the%20Indian%20innings.%20The%20duo%20put%20on%20a%2067-run%20partnership%20for%20the%20fourth%20wicket.%20But%20the%20Australians%20kept%20a%20check%20on%20the%20Indian%20batters.%20The%20Indian%20duo%20took%20minimal%20risk%20and%20failed%20to%20take%20the%20attack%20to%20the%20Australians.%20In%20the%2011%20to%2020%20overs%20phase%2C%20India%20could%20only%20accumulate%20only%2035%20runs%20for%20a%20loss%20of%20one%20wicket.%20In%20the%2021%20to%2030%20overs%20phase%2C%20India%20could%20score%20only%2037%20runs%20for%20the%20loss%20of%20one%20wicket.%20Overall%2C%20India%20scored%20only%2013%20boundaries%20and%20three%20sixes%20in%20the%20entire%20innings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHolding%20back%20Suryakumar%20Yadav%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndian%20batters%20struggled%20to%20score%20on%20a%20slow%20pitch%20and%20were%20148%2F4%20at%20one%20stage.%20Virat%20Kohli%20had%20just%20departed%20for%20a%2063-ball%2054.%20Everyone%20expected%20Suryakumar%20Yadav%20to%20join%20KL%20Rahul%20in%20the%20middle%2C%20yet%2C%20to%20the%20surprise%20of%20many%2C%20Ravindra%20Jadeja%20took%20the%20crease.%20The%20all-rounder%20was%20expected%20to%20accelerate%20India's%20run%20rate%2C%20but%20Jadeja%20could%20only%20muster%20a%2022-ball%209%20before%20returning%20to%20the%20pavilion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20hindsight%2C%20it%20appears%20India%20missed%20an%20opportunity%20by%20not%20sending%20Suryakumar%20Yadav%20up%20in%20the%20batting%20order.%20Renowned%20for%20his%20big-hitting%20prowess%2C%20had%20the%20Mumbai%20batter%20come%20in%20earlier%20and%20played%20in%20his%20characteristic%20style%2C%20India%20might%20have%20achieved%20a%20more%20formidable%20score%20on%20the%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENot%20bowling%20Mohammed%20Siraj%20early%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20India's%20impressive%2010-match%20winning%20streak%2C%20the%20bowlers%20played%20a%20pivotal%20role%20in%20securing%20victories.%20The%20pace%20combination%20of%20Jasprit%20Bumrah%20and%20Mohammed%20Siraj%20was%20particularly%20effective%20in%20providing%20early%20breakthroughs%20for%20the%20team.%20However%2C%20on%20the%20crucial%20day%2C%20Rohit%20Sharma%20opted%20to%20open%20the%20bowling%20with%20Bumrah%20and%20Mohammed%20Shami.%20While%20this%20decision%20led%20to%20a%20promising%20start%2C%20with%20Australia%20reduced%20to%2047%2F3%2C%20opting%20not%20to%20hand%20the%20new%20Mohammed%20Siraj%20proved%20detrimental%20for%20India.%20Siraj%2C%20known%20for%20his%20potency%20with%20the%20new%20ball%2C%20was%20less%20effective%20when%20brought%20in%20as%20the%20first%20change%2C%20especially%20bowling%20with%20a%20slightly%20older%20ball%20in%20the%20middle%20overs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENot%20going%20for%20the%20kill%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20had%20Australia%20reeling%20at%2047%2F3%20early%20on%20in%20defence%20of%20a%20modest%20total.%20Early%20breakthroughs%20by%20Jasprit%20Bumrah%20and%20Mohammed%20Shami%20rekindled%20India's%20prospects%20in%20the%20match.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20team%20couldn't%20capitalise%20on%20the%20advantageous%20situation.%20The%20Men%20in%20Blue%20failed%20to%20exert%20pressure%20on%20the%20opponent%20and%20conceded%20the%20momentum.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETravis%20Head%20(137)%20and%20Marnus%20Labuschagne%20(58)%20put%20on%20a%20192-run%20partnership%20for%20the%20fourth%20wicket%20to%20steer%20Australia%20out%20of%20danger%20and%20set%20them%20up%20for%20a%20historic%20sixth%20World%20Cup%20title.%20If%20India%20had%20seized%20the%20opportunity%20and%20capitalised%20on%20Australia's%20poor%20start%2C%20the%20outcome%20of%20the%20final%20could%20have%20been%20different%20for%20Rohit%20Sharma%20and%20Co.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700412540000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-11%2Fnevt3k38_rohit-sharma-afp_625x300_19_November_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Ficc-cricket-world-cup-2023%2Fwhere-india-lost-odi-cricket-world-cup-final-to-australia-five-turning-points-4587791%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20failed%20to%20go%20for%20the%20kill%20in%20their%20six-wicket%20loss%20to%20Australia%20in%20the%20World%20Cup%202023%20final.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A129%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Ficc-cricket-world-cup-2023%2Fwhere-india-lost-odi-cricket-world-cup-final-to-australia-five-turning-points-4587791%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Ficc-cricket-world-cup-2023%2Fwhere-india-lost-odi-cricket-world-cup-final-to-australia-five-turning-points-4587791%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Ficc-cricket-world-cup-2023%2Fwhere-india-lost-odi-cricket-world-cup-final-to-australia-five-turning-points-4587791%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Israel%20hopeful%20of%20Hamas%20deal%20to%20release%20hostages%20in%20'coming%20days'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700412508000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F6316%2Fproduction%2F_131766352_gettyimages-1740559620-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-middle-east-67469106%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%20comes%20after%20Qatar's%20PM%20said%20%26quot%3Bvery%20minor%26quot%3B%20obstacles%20remained%20to%20a%20deal%20between%20Israel%20and%20Hamas.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A104%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-middle-east-67469106%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-middle-east-67469106.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-middle-east-67469106.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Researchers%20explored%20pitch-black%20pits%20in%20Yucat%C3%A1n's%20labyrinthine%20underwater%20caves%20to%20unlock%20the%20secrets%20of%20the%20rivers%20that%20provide%20drinking%20water%20to%20millions%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22634%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20diver%20in%20blue%20swims%20among%20stalagmites%20and%20stalactites%20in%20the%20Yucat%C3%A1n's%20underwater%20caves%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6557f1aa22cf74a57399c523%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22823%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDivers%20swam%20throughout%20Yucat%C3%A1n's%20underwater%20caves%20taking%20samples%20of%20the%20different%20microbes%20that%20live%20there.%3Cp%3ENatalie%20Gibb%2FUnder%20the%20Jungle%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Yucat%C3%A1n%20Peninsula's%20underwater%20caves%20cover%20over%20900%20miles.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIts%20cenotes%2C%20or%20sinkholes%2C%20are%20an%20important%20drinking%20water%20resource%20for%20the%20region.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EResearchers%20mapped%20unique%20communities%20of%20microbes%20in%20a%20dozen%20areas%20of%20the%20cave%20system.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Sac%20Actun%20cave%20system%20on%20Mexico's%20Yucat%C3%A1n%20Peninsula%20contains%20many%20wonders%2C%20from%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnova-doc-13000-skeleton-found-in-mexico-is-critical-to-human-history-2018-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E13%2C000-year-old%20skeleton%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsac-actun-flooded-cave-under-threat-2018-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehuman%20artifacts%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20fossils%20of%20giant%20sloths.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20part%20of%20the%20Yucat%C3%A1n%20Peninsula%20Aquifer.%20Its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftulum-cenotes-are-polluted-as-construction-booms-for-digital-nomads-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecenotes%2C%20or%3C%2Fu%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cu%3E%20%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cu%3Ewater-filled%20sinkholes%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20provide%20drinking%20water%20for%20millions%20of%20people%20in%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCaves%20%E2%80%94%20and%20especially%20these%20caves%20%E2%80%94%20are%20really%20important%20groundwater%20resources%20for%20everyone%20that%20lives%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20Magdalena%20R.%20Osburn%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20Earth%20and%20planetary%20sciences%20at%20Northwestern%20University%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20and%20several%20colleagues%20at%20Northwestern%20University%20mapped%20communities%20of%20bacteria%20and%20other%20microbes%20that%20live%20in%20the%20aquifer's%20waters%2C%20from%20methane-producing%20methanogens%20to%20sunlight-loving%20cyanobacteria.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20an%20important%20first%20step%20to%20understanding%20how%20the%20microbes%20function%20and%20how%20to%20keep%20the%20crucial%20aquifer%20healthy.%20They%20published%20their%20findings%20in%20the%20peer-reviewed%20journal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.asm.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1128%2Faem.01682-23%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EApplied%20and%20Environmental%20Microbiology%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20underwater%20cave%20microbial%20community%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cave%20system%20is%20a%20network%20of%20over%20900%20miles%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eof%20connected%20caves%20that%20contain%20a%20mix%20of%20freshwater%20and%20saltwater.%20The%20Yucat%C3%A1n%20Peninsula%20is%20a%20giant%20limestone%20platform%2C%20Osburn%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20have%20a%20land%20surface%20that's%20built%20of%20a%20porous%20and%20dissolvable%20rock%2C%20you%20end%20up%20with%20caves%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20system%20has%20isolated%20reservoirs%2C%20dark%20pits%2C%20and%20sections%20exposed%20to%20the%20sun.%20It%20took%20a%20team%20of%20scientists%2C%20including%20half%20a%20dozen%20divers%2C%20to%20collect%20the%20samples%20and%20sequence%20the%20microbes'%20DNA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22970%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20diver%20holds%20a%20bottle%20to%20take%20a%20water%20sample%20in%20the%20Yucat%C3%A1n's%20underwater%20caves%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6557f2294ca513d8242bdccc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22650%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGetting%20a%20sterile%20sample%20underwater%20can%20be%20tricky.%3Cp%3ENatalie%20Gibb%2FUnder%20the%20Jungle%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20taking%2078%20samples%20from%20a%20dozen%20sites%2C%20they%20found%20different%20niches%20with%20different%20organisms.%20Caves%20flooded%20with%20coastal%20seawater%20had%20different%20microbes%20than%20The%20Pit%2C%20a%20deep%20cenote%20exposed%20to%20the%20surface%2C%20for%20example.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20interesting%20part%20was%20that%20different%20types%20of%20organisms%20in%20different%20environments%20were%20all%20performing%20similar%20functions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20found%20that%20often%20the%20ecological%20roles%20were%20being%20performed%20by%20different%20organisms%20in%20different%20sites%2C%20but%20those%20roles%20were%20always%20being%20performed%2C%26quot%3B%20Osburn%20said.%20These%20functions%20help%20balance%20the%20environment's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrobiome-based-drugs-in-development-seres-second-genome-2018-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emicrobiome%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EPreserving%20a%20critical%20water%20source%20for%20millions%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOsburn%20hopes%20future%20samples%20will%20allow%20them%20to%20sequence%20more%20of%20the%20microbes'%20genes%20to%20learn%20more%20about%20their%20specific%20functions%20within%20these%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20consistent%20bacteria%20showed%20up%20all%20over%20the%20place.%20Comamonadaceae%20were%20found%20in%20several%20locations%2C%20playing%20different%20roles%20and%20teaming%20up%20with%20various%20microbes.%20%26quot%3BThat%20one%20had%20different%20partners%20depending%20on%20which%20cave%20system%20you%20were%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20Osburn%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20could%20mean%20Comamonadaceae%20bacteria%20function%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bkeystone%20species%26quot%3B%20whose%20presence%20is%20fundamental%20to%20the%20health%20of%20the%20ecosystem%2C%20the%20authors%20wrote%20in%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20happens%20in%20these%20underground%20river%20systems%20is%20directly%20important%20to%20the%20drinking%20water%20of%20the%20populations%20that%20live%20above.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20she%20noted%20that%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-environmentalists-are-fighting-against-mexicos-new-maya-train-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eplanned%20train%20system%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Canc%C3%BAn%20to%20the%20Yucat%C3%A1n%20Peninsula%20could%20affect%20the%20cave%20system.%20One%20concern%20is%20that%20diesel%20could%20leak%20into%20cenotes%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Famericas%2Fcollapse-contamination-mexican-scientists-sound-alarm-mayan-train-2023-01-04%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReuters%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BGroundwater%20contamination%20is%20always%20a%20concern%2C%26quot%3B%20Osburn%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20introduction%20of%20any%20type%20of%20new%20substance%2C%20like%20diesel%2C%20or%20organic%20matter%2C%20like%20human%20waste%2C%20can%20influence%20a%20microbial%20community%2C%20Osburn%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20organic%20matter%20is%20going%20to%20be%20oxidized%2C%20either%20with%20oxygen%20or%20with%20things%20like%20sulfate%20or%20nitrate%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20end%20product%20of%20those%20are%20things%20like%20ammonia%20and%20things%20like%20sulfide%20or%20organic%20nitrogen%20compounds.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20those%20pollute%20drinking%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChemicals%20from%20medication%2C%20drugs%2C%20shampoo%2C%20and%20other%20sources%20have%20been%20showing%20up%20in%20the%20aquifer%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fphys.org%2Fnews%2F2011-02-pollutants-aquifers-threaten-future-mexico.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2011%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20found.%20As%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpartying-yachts-drugs-remote-work-destroying-worlds-most-instagrammable-destinations-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edigital%20nomads%20flock%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20peninsula%2C%20the%20contamination%20will%20likely%20get%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20potential%20for%20contamination%20is%20a%20problem%20anywhere%20there%20are%20caves%2C%20Osburn%20said.%20In%20Kentucky%2C%20she%20said%2C%20where%20she's%20done%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcool-geography-facts-us-2019-5%23located-in-kentucky-mammoth-cave-is-the-worlds-longest-known-cave-system-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ea%20lot%20of%20caving%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20people%20once%20treated%20sinkholes%20like%20landfills%20%E2%80%94%20throwing%20in%20everything%2C%20even%20the%20kitchen%20sink.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20big%20storm%2C%20Osburn%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20underground%20rivers%20flood%2C%20and%20then%20you%20find%20washing%20machines%20in%20caves%20because%20they%20don't%20just%20go%20away%20when%20you%20put%20them%20in%20the%20sinkhole.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyucatan-peninsula-underwater-caves-microbe-communities-microbiome-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700412435000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655a39d84ca513d8242bf835%3Ffo