%20how%20they%20could%20start%20a%20new%20AI%20company%2C%20the%20person%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20possibilities%20of%20a%20return%20or%20a%20restart%20for%20Altman%2C%20seen%20by%20many%20as%20the%20face%20of%20generative%20AI%2C%20are%20in%20flux%2C%20said%20the%20source%2C%20who%20asked%20not%20to%20be%20named%20because%20the%20source%20was%20not%20authorized%20to%20speak%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20parties%20involved.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20and%20Altman%20did%20not%20reply%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInvestors%20in%20OpenAI%2C%20including%20its%20biggest%20backer%20Microsoft%2C%20are%20discussing%20damage%20control%2C%20including%20possibly%20pushing%20the%20board%20to%20restore%20Altman%20as%20CEO%2C%20fearing%20a%20mass%20exodus%20of%20talent%20without%20him%2C%20other%20sources%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKhosla%20Ventures%2C%20an%20early%20backer%20of%20OpenAI%2C%20wants%20Altman%20back%20at%20OpenAI%20but%20%26quot%3Bwill%20back%20him%20in%20whatever%20he%20does%20next%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20fund's%20founder%20Vinod%20Khosla%20posted%20on%20X%20on%20Saturday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMicrosoft%20declined%20to%20comment.%20It%20reportedly%20owns%2049%25%20of%20the%20company%2C%20while%20other%20investors%20and%20employees%20control%2049%25%2C%20with%202%25%20owned%20by%20OpenAI's%20nonprofit%20parent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEmotions%20ran%20high%20on%20Saturday%20as%20current%20and%20former%20employees%20were%20angered%20by%20Altman's%20sacking%20and%20worried%20over%20how%20an%20upcoming%20%2486%20billion%20share%20sale%20could%20be%20affected%20by%20the%20sudden%20management%20upheaval.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOpenAI%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20co-founded%20by%20billionaire%20Elon%20Musk%2C%20launched%20ChatGPT%20on%20Nov.%2030%20last%20year%2C%20setting%20off%20a%20global%20sensation%20over%20generative%20AI%20technology%20that%20quickly%20became%20the%20world's%20fastest-growing%20software%20application.%20It%20set%20off%20a%20wave%20of%