20the%20entry%20point%20is%20%2445%2C000-plus%2C%20that's%20still%20steep%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Cspan%3EVince%20Sheehy%2C%20a%20car%20dealer%20in%20the%20Washington%2C%20D.C.%20area%2C%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcadillac-to-launch-new-entry-level-ev-in-2024-otpiq-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700402298000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655a00239c7d23cb3b9d1de4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcadillac-to-launch-new-entry-level-ev-in-2024-otpiq-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20new%20vehicle%2C%20named%20Optiq%2C%20is%20being%20marketed%20by%20the%20US%20automaker%20as%20a%20cheaper%20alternative%20to%20its%20three%20luxury%20EVs.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22pthompson%40insider.com%20(Polly%20Thompson)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A99%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcadillac-to-launch-new-entry-level-ev-in-2024-otpiq-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20Do%20US%20Sanctions%20on%20Russia's%20Arctic%20LNG%202%20Project%20Mean%20for%20the%20World%20Energy%20Order%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F19192144%2Fbelokameka-LNG-center.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20bouts%20of%20sanctions%20the%20United%20States%20recently%20imposed%20on%20Russia%20apparently%20signal%20a%20strategic%20shift%20in%20the%20world%20energy%20order.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.state.gov%2Ftaking-additional-sweeping-measures-against-russia%2F%5C%22%3EThe%20latest%20sanctions%20on%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20Arctic%20liquefied%20national%20gas%20(LNG)%202%20project%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20imposed%20as%20a%20penalty%20for%20its%20war%20on%20Ukraine%20%E2%80%93%20have%20different%20ramifications.%20Insofar%20as%20a%20new%20geopolitical%20dynamic%20takes%20shape%20in%20the%20already%20volatile%20Arctic%20region%2C%20Washington%20appears%20determined%20to%20prevent%20Russia%20from%20gaining%20prominence%20in%20the%20global%20energy%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDoes%20the%20emerging%20strategic%20landscape%20%E2%80%93%20with%20the%20continuing%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20the%20new%20spell%20of%20war%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20%E2%80%93%20augur%20well%20for%20the%20international%20correlation%20of%20power%20dynamic%2C%20with%20all%20its%20attendant%20implications%20for%20the%20global%20energy%20supply%20chains%3F%20Though%20it%20is%20too%20early%20to%20suggest%20a%20quick%20revival%2Freversal%20in%20the%20coming%20months%2C%20the%20global%20market%20is%20expected%20to%20grapple%20with%20disruptions%20and%20shortfalls%20in%20the%20energy%20sector%2C%20in%20one%20way%20or%20the%20other.%20Perceptibly%2C%20the%20United%20States%20is%20poised%20to%20take%20the%20lead%20and%20dictate%20the%20terms%20of%20energy%20trade%20in%20the%20coming%20decades.%20The%20sanctions%20on%20the%20Arctic%20LNG%202%20are%20believed%20to%20be%20a%20precursor%20of%20this%20changing%20scenario.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EObviously%2C%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2023%2F03%2F03%2Fceraweek-how-russias-war-made-the-us-a-dominant-supplier-of-energy-.html%5C%22%3Ereshaped%20global%20energy%20supply%20chains%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20propelling%20the%20US%20to%20the%20forefront%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20energy-exporting%20nations.%20As%20Europe%20faced%20challenges%20in%20its%20natural%20gas%20imports%20from%20Russia%2C%20US%20exporters%20redirected%20shipments%20of%20LNG%20from%20Asia%20to%20Europe.%20With%20Russian%20oil%20under%20sanctions%20and%20the%20European%20Union%20rejecting%20Moscow%E2%80%99s%20seaborne%20cargoes%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20substantial%20increase%20in%20US%20crude%20and%20refined%20product%20exports%20to%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20shift%20marked%20a%20significant%20transformation%2C%20with%20the%20US%20evolving%20from%20a%20supplier%20of%20%E2%80%9Cmilitary%20arsenal%E2%80%9D%20to%20a%20major%20energy%20arsenal%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2023%2F03%2F03%2Fceraweek-how-russias-war-made-the-us-a-dominant-supplier-of-energy-.html%5C%22%3Enoted%20by%20John%20Kilduff%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20partner%20at%20Again%20Capital.%20Already%2C%20indications%20in%20this%20direction%20have%20come%20from%20US%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.state.gov%2Fdigital-press-briefing-with-geoffrey-r-pyatt-assistant-secretary-of-state-for-energy-resources%2F%5C%22%3Especial%20briefing%20on%20October%2013%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Geoffrey%20R.%20Pyatt%2C%20assistant%20secretary%20of%20state%20for%20energy%20resources%2C%20said%20that%20the%20US%20was%20%E2%80%9Ccommitted%20to%20working%20in%20lockstep%20both%20to%20impose%20a%20price%20on%20Russia%20for%20its%20brutal%20invasion%2C%20but%20also%20to%20ensure%20that%20we%20deny%20Putin%20the%20resources%20that%20he%20is%20using%20in%20order%20to%20prosecute%20this%20terrible%20war%20against%20the%20people%20of%20Ukraine%E2%80%9D.%20And%20in%20the%20case%20of%20its%20G7%20partners%20in%20particular%2C%20the%20US%20is%20%E2%80%9Calso%20committed%20to%20working%20jointly%20to%20deny%20Russia%20future%20energy%20revenues%20and%20to%20target%20in%20particular%20investments%20and%20projects%20which%20are%20aimed%20at%20growing%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20future%20energy%20revenue%E2%80%9D.%20Pyatt%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CThat%20is%20the%20reason%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20why%20you%20saw%20our%20last%20sanctions%20package%20including%20measures%20specifically%20targeting%20the%20Arctic%20LNG%202%20project%20in%20Russia.%20Our%20aim%20there%2C%20again%2C%20is%20to%20deny%20Russia%20future%20energy%20revenue.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20October%2024%2C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.state.gov%2Fassistant-secretary-geoffrey-pyatt-north-american-gas-forum%2F%5C%22%3E%C2%A0Pyatt%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CRussia%E2%80%99s%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20overturned%20the%20international%20energy%20order.%E2%80%9D%20With%20%E2%80%9CRussia%E2%80%99s%20weaponisation%20of%20its%20oil%20and%20gas%20resources%2C%20%E2%80%A6%20%5Bit%5D%20is%20never%20going%20to%20be%20viewed%20again%20as%20a%20reliable%20energy%20supplier.%E2%80%9D%20Pyatt%20%C2%A0pointed%20out%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20remarkable%20success%20with%20which%20Europe%20has%20de-risked%20its%20dependency%20on%20Russian%20gas%E2%80%9D.%20He%20said%20%E2%80%9CAmerican%20producers%20have%20played%20an%20indispensable%20role%20in%20helping%20to%20fulfil%20European%20energy%20security%20%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPyatt%20further%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CRussia%20which%20until%202022%20was%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20largest%20oil%20and%20gas%20exporter%2C%20has%20now%20put%20itself%20more%20or%20less%20permanently%20into%20the%20penalty%20box.%20And%20I%20think%20however%20and%20whenever%20the%20tragedy%20in%20Ukraine%20comes%20to%20an%20end%2C%20the%20market%20is%20never%20again%20going%20to%20look%20at%20Russia%20as%20a%20reliable%20investment%20location%20or%20look%20at%20Russia%20as%20a%20reliable%20supplier.%20So%20that%20means%E2%80%A6there%20is%20going%20to%20be%20continued%20demand%20for%20energy%20that%20the%20United%20States%20produces.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20interaction%20with%20James%20O%E2%80%99Brien%20and%20Pyatt%20on%20November%208%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.murphy.senate.gov%2Fnewsroom%2Fpress-releases%2Fmurphy-this-is-an-existential-moment-for-ukraine%23%3A~%3Atext%3D%25E2%2580%259CBut%2520the%2520IEA%2520projects%2520Russia%2527s%2Cin%2520oil%2520and%2520gas%2520revenue.%5C%22%3EUS%20Senator%20Chris%20Murphy%3C%2Fa%3E%20spoke%20at%20a%20US%20Senate%20Foreign%20Relations%20Committee%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foreign.senate.gov%2Fhearings%2Fus-national-security-interests-in-ukraine%5C%22%3Ehearing%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20U.S.%20national%20security%20interests%20in%20Ukraine.%20He%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CBut%20the%20IEA%20projects%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20share%20of%20globally%20traded%20oil%20is%20going%20to%20fall%20by%2050%25%20by%202030%2C%20and%20their%20net%20income%20from%20gas%20sales%20is%20going%20to%20fall%20from%20%2475%20billion%20to%20%2430%20billion.%20You%E2%80%99re%20spending%20already%206%25%20of%20your%20GDP%2C%20and%20you%20have%20a%20potentially%20catastrophic%20fall%20coming%20in%20oil%20and%20gas%20revenue.%20That%20is%20one%20of%20the%20things%2C%20maybe%20the%20primary%20factor%20that%20may%20push%20Russia%20to%20the%20table%20to%20try%20to%20drive%20a%20conclusion%20to%20this%20conflict.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.state.gov%2Fassistant-secretary-geoffrey-pyatt-north-american-gas-forum%2F%5C%22%3EPyatt%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20however%2C%20pointed%20out%20that%20there%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Cstructural%20decline%20in%20oil%20and%20gas%20revenue%20that%20Russia%20is%20confronting%E2%80%9D.%20He%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20working%20as%20hard%20as%20we%20can%20to%20accelerate%20that%20trend.%20We%20do%20that%20through%20two%20mechanisms%3B%20One%20is%20by%20accelerating%20our%20energy%20transition%2C%20both%20here%20in%20the%20United%20States%20but%20also%20globally%2C%20as%20the%20Biden%20administration%20has%20done%20through%20the%20Inflation%20Reduction%20Act%20to%20reduce%20the%20dependence%20on%20fossil%20fuels.%20%E2%80%A6But%20the%20other%20aspect%20of%20this%20is%20what%20we%20are%20doing%20systematically%20to%20reduce%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20future%20energy%20revenue.%20Just%20last%20week%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20we%20levelled%20new%20sanctions%20against%20a%20project%20in%20the%20Arctic%2C%20Arctic%20LNG%202%2C%20which%20is%20Novatech%E2%80%99s%20flagship%20LNG%20project%2C%20which%20Novatech%20set%20in%20motion%20with%20the%20aspiration%20of%20developing%20Russia%20as%20the%20largest%20LNG%20exporter%20in%20the%20world.%20Our%20objective%20is%20to%20kill%20that%20project.%20And%20we%E2%80%99re%20doing%20that%20through%20our%20sanctions%20working%20with%20our%20partners%20in%20the%20G7%20and%20beyond.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EArctic%20LNG%202%20project%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnewsukraine.rbc.ua%2Fnews%2Fu-s-wants-to-kill-russian-gas-project-arctic-1699476181.html%5C%22%3EThe%20Arctic%20LNG%202%20project%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20managed%20by%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20Novatek%2C%20focuses%20on%20natural%20gas%20extraction%20and%20liquefied%20natural%20gas%20(LNG)%20production.%20On%20November%202%2C%20the%20US%20included%20the%20Arctic%20LNG%202%20project%20into%20its%20sanctions%20list%2C%20targeting%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20energy%20sector%20production%20and%20export%20capabilities.%20The%20project%20is%20run%20by%20LLC%20Arctic%20LNG%202%2C%20a%20joint%20venture%20with%20PJSC%20NOVATEK%20(60%25)%2C%20TotalEnergies%20consortium%20(10%25)%2C%20Chinese%20corporations%20CNPC%20(10%25)%20and%20CNOOC%20(10%25)%2C%20and%20JAPAN%20ARCTIC%20LNG%20(a%20consortium%20of%20Japanese%20companies%20MITSUI%20and%20JOGMEC)%20(10%25).%20These%20sanctions%20are%20part%20of%20a%20broader%20punitive%20measures%20by%20the%20US%20against%20Russia%2C%20emerging%20from%20the%20full-scale%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENovatek%20has%20been%20actively%20advancing%20the%20Arctic%20LNG-2%20project%2C%20a%20significant%20initiative%20aimed%20at%20substantially%20increasing%20LNG%20production.%20The%20project%20is%20envisaged%20to%20elevate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsputnikglobe.com%2F20230722%2Fsecond-to-none-arctic-lng-2-to-boost-russias-share-in-world-energy-market-1112063345.html%5C%22%3ERussia%E2%80%99s%20global%20market%20share%20in%20LNG%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%2020%25%2C%20and%20particularly%20it%20stands%20as%20a%20one-of-a-kind%20undertaking%20on%20a%20global%20scale.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussian%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsputnikglobe.com%2F20230722%2Fsecond-to-none-arctic-lng-2-to-boost-russias-share-in-world-energy-market-1112063345.html%5C%22%3EPresident%20Vladimir%20Putin%3C%2Fa%3E%20launched%20the%20first%20completed%20production%20line%20for%20LNG%20on%20a%20gravity-based%20platform%20within%20the%20Arctic%20LNG-2%20project%2C%20situated%20in%20Murmansk.%20This%20colossal%20platform%2C%20weighing%20over%20600%2C000%20tonnes%2C%20is%20set%20to%20be%20pushed%20along%20the%20Northern%20Sea%20Route%20to%20the%20Utrenneye%20field%20on%20the%20Gydan%20Peninsula%20in%20the%20Yamal-Nenets%20Autonomous%20Area.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUpon%20the%20full%20realisation%20of%20the%20project%2C%20Arctic%20LNG-2%20will%20feature%20three%20liquefaction%20trains%20capable%20of%20producing%20a%20total%20of%2019.8%20million%20tonnes%20per%20annum%20(MTPA)%20of%20LNG%2C%20along%20with%20up%20to%201.6%20MTPA%20of%20stable%20gas%20condensate%20(SGC).%20The%20scale%20and%20uniqueness%20of%20this%20endeavour%20underscore%20its%20significance%20in%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20strategy%20to%20enhance%20its%20presence%20in%20the%20global%20LNG%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsputnikglobe.com%2F20230722%2Fsecond-to-none-arctic-lng-2-to-boost-russias-share-in-world-energy-market-1112063345.html%5C%22%3ERussia%20has%20dismissed%20the%20impact%20of%20Western%20sanctions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20asserting%20that%20they%20are%20employed%20by%20the%20United%20States%20to%20eliminate%20Moscow%20as%20a%20competitor%20in%20the%20global%20energy%20supplies%20arena.%20These%20sanctions%20do%20not%20directly%20apply%20to%20the%20project%20or%20its%20shareholders.%20However%2C%20concerns%20were%20raised%20about%20potential%20complications%20in%20how%20Mitsui%20and%20JOGMEC%20provide%20support%20for%20the%20project%2C%20possibly%20leading%20to%20delays%20in%20production%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsputnikglobe.com%2F20230722%2Fsecond-to-none-arctic-lng-2-to-boost-russias-share-in-world-energy-market-1112063345.html%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20Russian%20sources%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Arctic%20LNG-2%20project%20is%20distinguished%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsputnikglobe.com%2F20230722%2Fsecond-to-none-arctic-lng-2-to-boost-russias-share-in-world-energy-market-1112063345.html%5C%22%3Eseveral%20key%20features%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20represents%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20inaugural%20initiative%20for%20the%20serial%20production%20of%20liquefied%20natural%20gas%20(LNG)%20lines%20based%20on%20gravity-based%20structures%20(GBS).%20The%20utilisation%20of%20this%20construction%20technology%2C%20coupled%20with%20the%20substantial%20localization%20of%20equipment%20and%20material%20production%20in%20Russia%2C%20ensures%20cost-effectiveness%2C%20boosting%20the%20competitiveness%20of%20Russian%20LNG%20globally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Russia%2C%20Arctic%20LNG-2%20also%20adheres%20to%20high%20environmental%20standards%2C%20as%20the%20GBS%20construction%20eliminates%20the%20need%20for%20a%20liquefaction%20plant%20at%20the%20production%20site.%20Instead%2C%20LNG%20lines%20are%20linked%20from%20the%20Murmansk%20region%20to%20the%20Yamal%20field%20along%20the%20Northern%20Sea%20Route%20(NSR)%2C%20thereby%20reducing%20environmental%20impact.%20Furthermore%2C%20the%20project%20enhances%20energy%20efficiency%2C%20resulting%20in%20a%20more%20than%2030%25%20reduction%20in%20greenhouse%20gas%20emissions%20per%20tonne%20of%20LNG%20compared%20to%20the%20industry%20average.%20This%20positions%20Russia%20favourably%20amid%20the%20global%20transition%20to%20a%20low-carbon%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20successful%20commissioning%20of%20Arctic%20LNG-2%20is%20anticipated%20to%20significantly%20increase%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20overall%20LNG%20production%2C%20accounting%20for%20over%20half%20of%20the%20load%20of%20the%20NSR%20by%202030%2C%20as%20projected%20by%20the%20Russian%20government.%20Moreover%2C%20the%20project%20contributes%20to%20the%20development%20of%20the%20Russian%20Arctic%20economy%2C%20involving%20numerous%20domestic%20enterprises%20and%20creating%20over%2080%2C000%20jobs%20across%20the%20country.%20Arctic%20LNG-2%20represents%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20third%20LNG%20project%2C%20following%20the%20Sakhalin-2%20project%20launched%20in%20February%202009%20and%20the%20Yamal%20LNG%20project%20initiated%20in%20December%202017.%20Upon%20completion%2C%20Arctic%20LNG-2%20is%20expected%20to%20contribute%20approximately%2019.8%20million%20tonnes%20per%20year%2C%20equivalent%20to%2027%20billion%20cubic%20meters%20of%20gas%20annually%2C%20according%20to%20Konstantin%20Simonov%2C%20the%20director-general%20of%20the%20National%20Energy%20Security%20Fund.%20Russia%20is%20not%20only%20a%20major%20producer%20of%20LNG%20but%20also%20a%20significant%20supplier%20of%20pipeline%20gas%2C%20solidifying%20its%20position%20as%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20energy%20producers%20globally.%20Despite%20facing%20Western%20energy%20embargoes%20in%20response%20to%20the%20commencement%20of%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20Russia%20continues%20to%20supply%20more%20gas%20to%20world%20markets%2C%20both%20in%20pipeline%20and%20liquefied%20forms%2C%20according%20to%20Simonov.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20major%20consumers%20of%20LNG%20are%20primarily%20Asian%20countries%2C%20including%20China%2C%20Japan%2C%20South%20Korea%20and%20India.%20Spain%20and%20France%20are%20also%20significant%20European%20importers%20of%20Russian%20LNG%2C%20particularly%20from%20the%20Russian%20Arctic.%20The%20increased%20capacities%20of%20the%20Arctic%20LNG-2%20project%20are%20expected%20to%20amplify%20the%20volume%20of%20LNG%20deliveries%20to%20these%20countries%2C%20utilising%20the%20Northern%20Sea%20Route%20(NSR)%20as%20a%20strategic%20transit%20route.%20This%20expansion%20aims%20to%20enhance%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20position%20in%20the%20global%20gas%20market%2C%20enabling%20it%20to%20manage%20the%20challenges%20of%20reconfiguring%20gas%20exports%20in%20the%20current%20geopolitical%20and%20economic%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWestern%20sanctions%20have%20presented%20new%20challenges%20for%20Novatek%2C%20the%20operator%20of%20the%20Arctic%20LNG%202%20project%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsputnikglobe.com%2F20230722%2Fsecond-to-none-arctic-lng-2-to-boost-russias-share-in-world-energy-market-1112063345.html%5C%22%3Eoutlined%20by%20Simonov%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20primary%20segment%20of%20the%20first%20line%20of%20Arctic%20LNG%202%20was%20produced%20before%20the%20imposition%20of%20sanctions%20on%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20LNG%20industry.%20Novatek%20had%20utilised%20technologies%20from%20the%20German%20company%20Linde%2C%20with%20other%20foreign%20suppliers%2C%20including%20the%20American%20company%20Baker%20Hughes%2C%20also%20contributing%20to%20the%20project.%20However%2C%20post-sanctions%2C%20Baker%20Hughes%20refused%20to%20supply%20the%20full%20number%20of%20turbines%20required%20for%20the%20project.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsputnikglobe.com%2F20230722%2Fsecond-to-none-arctic-lng-2-to-boost-russias-share-in-world-energy-market-1112063345.html%5C%22%3ECritics%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20rather%20than%20hindering%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20industrial%20development%2C%20Western%20sanctions%20would%20serve%20as%20a%20catalyst%20for%20boosting%20domestic%20producers%20and%20technologies%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20is%20actively%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fbusiness%2Fenergy%2Fus-working-with-allies-over-sanctions-russian-arctic-lng-project-state-dept-2023-11-08%2F%5C%22%3Ecollaborating%20with%20partner%20countries%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20address%20sanctions%20on%20the%20Russian%20LNG%20project%20in%20the%20Arctic.%20The%20Office%20of%20Foreign%20Assets%20Control%2C%20a%20division%20of%20the%20Treasury%20Department%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fofac.treasury.gov%2Frecent-actions%2F20231102%5C%22%3Eissued%20a%20general%20license%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20permits%20the%20wind-down%20of%20transactions%20related%20to%20Arctic%20LNG-2.%20This%20authorisation%20is%20effective%20through%20January%2031%2C%202024.%20The%20spokesperson%20from%20the%20State%20Department%20emphasised%20ongoing%20coordination%20with%20partner%20nations%20as%20the%20January%20deadline%20approaches.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENovatek%20holds%20a%2060%25%20stake%20in%20the%20Arctic%20LNG-2%20project%20and%20aims%20to%20commence%20production%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year.%20This%20project%20is%20pivotal%20for%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20ambitions%20to%20secure%2020%25%20of%20the%20global%20LNG%20market%20by%202035%2C%20up%20from%20the%20current%208%25.%20The%20new%20sanctions%20on%20the%20Arctic%20LNG-2%20project%20are%20specifically%20targeted%20at%20degrading%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20future%20energy%20production%20and%20export%20capabilities%2C%20while%20ensuring%20the%20continued%20flow%20of%20energy%20to%20global%20markets%2C%20according%20to%20a%20spokesperson%20from%20the%20US%20State%20Department.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20spokesperson%20emphasised%20that%20the%20US%20does%20not%20have%20a%20strategic%20interest%20in%20reducing%20the%20global%20supply%20of%20energy%2C%20as%20this%20would%20lead%20to%20increased%20energy%20prices%20worldwide%2C%20benefiting%20Moscow.%20Despite%20the%20sanctions%2C%20the%20US%20maintained%20its%20position%20as%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20largest%20LNG%20exporter%20in%20the%20first%20six%20months%20of%20the%20current%20year%2C%20as%20reported%20by%20the%20Energy%20Information%20Administration.%20The%20State%20Department%20spokesperson%20underscored%20the%20importance%20of%20close%20coordination%20with%20partners%20on%20sanctions%20issues%20and%20affirmed%20the%20continuation%20of%20such%20collaboration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChanging%20energy%20landscape%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20world%20is%20currently%20grappling%20with%20different%20dimensions%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iea.org%2Freports%2Fworld-energy-outlook-2022%2Fexecutive-summary%5C%22%3Eenergy%20crisis%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20characterised%20by%20unprecedented%20challenges.%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20no%20doubt%20transformed%20the%20economic%20recovery%20from%20the%20pandemic%20into%20a%20full-fledged%20energy%20disorder.%20As%20the%20largest%20global%20exporter%20of%20fossil%20fuels%2C%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20restrictions%20on%20natural%20gas%20supply%20to%20Europe%2C%20coupled%20with%20European%20sanctions%20on%20Russian%20oil%20and%20coal%20imports%2C%20are%20disrupting%20a%20crucial%20route%20of%20global%20energy%20trade.%20While%20all%20fuels%20are%20impacted%2C%20gas%20markets%20are%20at%20the%20forefront%2C%20with%20Russia%20attempting%20to%20exert%20influence%20by%20subjecting%20countries%20to%20higher%20energy%20costs%20and%20supply%20deficits.%20Spot%20prices%20for%20natural%20gas%20skyrocketed%20to%20unprecedented%20levels.%20The%20soaring%20prices%20of%20gas%20and%20coal%20contributed%20significantly%20to%20a%2090%25%20increase%20in%20electricity%20costs%20worldwide.%20To%20compensate%20for%20the%20shortfall%20in%20Russian%20gas%20supply%2C%20Europe%20sought%20to%20import%20additional%20quantities%20of%20LNG.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKey%20players%20in%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20gas%20production%20include%20Gazprom%20and%20Novatek%2C%20while%20several%20oil%20companies%2C%20including%20Rosneft%2C%20also%20contribute%20to%20gas%20production.%20Gazprom%2C%20a%20state-owned%20entity%2C%20remains%20the%20largest%20gas%20producer%2C%20although%20its%20share%20has%20decreased%20over%20the%20past%20decade%20due%20to%20expansions%20by%20Novatek%20and%20Rosneft.%20Nevertheless%2C%20Gazprom%20still%20contributed%20to%2068%25%20of%20Russian%20gas%20production%20in%202021.%20Geographically%2C%20gas%20production%20has%20shifted%20from%20West%20Siberia%20to%20areas%20like%20Yamal%2C%20Eastern%20Siberia%2C%20the%20Far%20East%20and%20offshore%20Arctic%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia%E2%80%99s%20extensive%20gas%20export%20pipeline%20network%20includes%20transit%20routes%20through%20Belarus%20and%20Ukraine%2C%20as%20well%20as%20direct%20pipelines%20into%20Europe%20(such%20as%20Nord%20Stream%2C%20Blue%20Stream%20and%20TurkStream).%20The%20completion%20of%20the%20Nord%20Stream%20II%20pipeline%20in%202021%20faced%20challenges%20as%20the%20German%20government%20withheld%20certification%20following%20the%20Russian%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%20Russian%20natural%20gas%20accounted%20for%20a%20significant%20portion%20of%20European%20Union%20gas%20demand%2C%20representing%2045%25%20of%20imports%20and%20nearly%2040%25%20of%20demand%20in%202021%2C%20with%20Germany%2C%20Turkey%20and%20Italy%20as%20the%20primary%20importers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia%E2%80%99s%20strategic%20initiatives%20include%20the%20Power%20of%20Siberia%20pipeline%2C%20a%20major%20eastward%20gas%20export%20pipeline%20connecting%20far%20east%20fields%20directly%20to%20China.%20With%20a%20capacity%20of%2038%20bcm%2C%20it%20aims%20to%20gradually%20increase%20exports%20to%2038%20bcm%20in%20the%20coming%20years.%20Russia%20is%20also%20contemplating%20the%20development%20of%20the%20Power%20of%20Siberia-2%20pipeline%2C%20which%20could%20supply%20China%20from%20West%20Siberian%20gas%20fields.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDiversification%20efforts%20extend%20to%20LNG%20development%2C%20with%20Russia%20targeting%20110-190%20bcm%2Fyear%20LNG%20exports%20by%202025.%20In%202021%2C%20Russia%20ranked%20as%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20fourth-largest%20LNG%20exporter%2C%20shipping%2040%20bcm%20and%20constituting%20around%208%25%20of%20global%20LNG%20supply.%20Also%2C%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20focus%20on%20the%20Arctic%20aims%20to%20boost%20oil%20and%20gas%20production%2C%20leveraging%20over%2080%25%20of%20natural%20gas%20production%20and%20an%20estimated%2020%25%20of%20crude%20production.%20While%20climate%20change%20poses%20challenges%2C%20it%20also%20opens%20opportunities%20for%20expanded%20access%20to%20Arctic%20trade%20routes%2C%20enhancing%20flexibility%20in%20seaborne%20fossil%20fuel%20deliveries%2C%20especially%20to%20Asia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frussiancouncil.ru%2Fen%2Farcticoil%23russia%5C%22%3Eestimates%20from%20both%20the%20Organisation%20of%20the%20Petroleum%20Exporting%20Countries%20(OPEC)%20and%20the%20International%20Energy%20Agency%20(IEA)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20global%20energy%20demand%20is%20expected%20to%20increase%20by%2040-60%25%20by%202040%20compared%20to%202010%20levels.%20In%20this%20future%20energy%20landscape%2C%20oil%20is%20anticipated%20to%20maintain%20a%20leading%20role%2C%20constituting%2025-27%25%20of%20the%20total%20supply%2C%20while%20gas%20will%20make%20up%2024%E2%80%9326%25%20(compared%20to%20today%E2%80%99s%20figures%20of%2035%25%20and%2026%25%2C%20respectively).%20Notably%2C%20a%20significant%20portion%20of%20oil%20and%20gas%20production%20in%202040%20is%20projected%20to%20occur%20in%20deposits%20that%20have%20yet%20to%20be%20explored.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20these%20forecasts%20and%20considering%20the%20potential%20of%20undiscovered%20oil%20and%20gas%20reserves%20in%20the%20Arctic%20Shelf%2C%20estimated%20at%2090%20billion%20barrels%20of%20oil%20and%2047%20trillion%20cubic%20meters%20of%20natural%20gas%2C%20the%20offshore%20resources%20in%20the%20Arctic%20could%20play%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20sustaining%20current%20production%20levels%20and%20fostering%20future%20growth%20in%20the%20medium%20and%20long%20term.%20This%20underscores%20the%20strategic%20importance%20of%20the%20Arctic%20region%20in%20meeting%20global%20energy%20demands%20and%20shaping%20the%20future%20of%20the%20oil%20and%20gas%20industry.%20However%2C%20with%20the%20new%20sanctions%20in%20place%2C%20and%20as%20Washington%E2%80%99s%20ambitious%20energy%20drive%20gets%20underway%2C%20it%20remains%20to%20be%20seen%20if%20Russia%20will%20be%20able%20to%20appropriate%20the%20oil%20and%20natural%20gas%20reserves%20in%20the%20Arctic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EK.M%20Seethi%2C%20an%20ICSSR%20Senior%20Fellow%2C%20is%20Academic%20Advisor%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ficps.mgu.ac.in%2Ffaculty%2F%5C%22%3EInternational%20Centre%20for%20Polar%20Studies%3C%2Fa%3E%20(ICPS)%20and%20Director%2C%20Inter%20University%20Centre%20for%20Social%20Science%20Research%20and%20Extension%20(IUCSSRE)%2C%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20University%2C%20Kerala.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700402014000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F19192144%2Fbelokameka-LNG-center.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenergy%2Fwhat-do-us-sanctions-on-russias-arctic-lng-2-project-mean-for-the-world-energy-order%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20US%20is%20poised%20to%20take%20the%20lead%20and%20dictate%20the%20terms%20of%20energy%20trade%20in%20the%20coming%20decades.%20The%20sanctions%20on%20the%20Arctic%20LNG%202%20are%20believed%20to%20be%20a%20precursor%20of%20this%20changing%20scenario.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenergy%2Fwhat-do-us-sanctions-on-russias-arctic-lng-2-project-mean-for-the-world-energy-order%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Emerald%20Fennell-Directed%20%E2%80%98Saltburn%E2%80%99%20Conjured%20Images%20of%20Dark%2C%20Bloody%20Comedy%2C%20Says%20Cinematographer%20Linus%20Sandgren%20at%20Camerimage%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700401527000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2FLinus-Sandgren.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235799938%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Cinematographer%20Linus%20Sandgren%20says%20he%20and%20director%20Emerald%20Fennell%20relied%20on%20their%20emotions%20and%20instincts%20to%20conjure%20the%20%E2%80%9Cgothic%E2%80%9D%20look%20o