rial_photo_of_Mostar_1996.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20popularity%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.al-monitor.com%2Foriginals%2F2023%2F11%2Fwhy-bin-ladens-letter-america-trending-during-gaza-war%5C%22%3EOsama%20bin%20Laden%E2%80%99s%20letter%3C%2Fa%3E%20justifying%20the%20September%2011%2C%202001%20attacks%20against%20the%20United%20States%20is%20a%20warning%20sign.%20In%20many%20ways%20the%20resurgence%20of%20interest%20in%20this%20forgotten%20man%20and%20his%20(largely%20decimated)%20terrorist%20organisation%20is%20not%20so%20much%20a%20sign%20of%20radicalisation%20as%20it%20is%20of%20confusion.%20As%20Israel%20continues%20its%20horrific%20war%20in%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20using%20the%20horrific%20attack%20of%20Hamas%20on%20October%207%20as%20the%20justification%2C%20most%20people%20are%20trying%20to%20desperately%20trying%20to%20make%20sense%20of%20the%20scenes%20they%20see%20every%20day%20of%20enormous%20human%20suffering.%20More%20importantly%2C%20they%20struggle%20to%20understand%20why%20the%20world%20%E2%80%93%20particularly%20the%20United%20States%20%E2%80%93%20is%20allowing%20and%20facilitating%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20a%20certain%20degree%20this%20is%20because%20of%20ignorance.%20People%20everywhere%20are%20quick%20to%20reach%20conclusions%20about%20faraway%20conflicts%20about%20which%20they%20know%20little%20versus%20ones%20close%20by%20about%20which%20they%20might%20know%20a%20little%20more.%20For%20example%2C%20Indians%20%E2%80%93%20with%20honourable%20exceptions%20%E2%80%93%20banging%20on%20about%20how%20easy%20it%20may%20be%20to%20resolve%20the%20issues%20in%20Israel-Palestine%20seem%20to%20be%20largely%20mum%20about%20the%20horrors%20of%20Manipur%20or%20our%20colonial%20policies%20in%20Kashmir.%20The%20Chinese%20are%20silent%20about%20Xinjiang%20and%20Tibet%2C%20Iranians%20about%20the%20rights%20of%20their%20own%20women%2C%20and%20so%20on%20and%20so%20forth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20is%20not%20the%20sum%20of%20things%2C%20and%20such%20rationalisations%20can%20easily%20descend%20into%20whataboutery.%20The%20scale%20of%20the%20carnage%20in%20this%20particular%20conflict%20is%20enormous.%20As%20Save%20the%20Children%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.savethechildren.net%2Fnews%2Fgaza-3195-children-killed-three-weeks-surpasses-annual-number-children-killed-conflict-zones%5C%22%3Estates%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20number%20of%20children%20reported%20killed%20in%20just%20three%20weeks%20in%20Gaza%20is%20more%20than%20the%20number%20killed%20in%20armed%20conflict%20globally%20%E2%80%93%20across%20more%20than%2020%20countries%20%E2%80%93%20over%20the%20course%20of%20a%20whole%20year.%E2%80%9D%20For%20a%20scale%20of%20reference%2C%20in%20that%20other%20conflict%2C%20the%20Russian%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fukraine.un.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2023-10%2FUkraine%2520-%2520civilian%2520casualty%2520update%2520as%2520of%25208%2520October%25202023%2520ENG.pdf%5C%22%3Eover%20500%20children%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20killed%20between%20February%2024%2C%202022%20and%20October%209%2C%202023.%20In%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20the%20number%20is%20about%204%2C000%20in%20five%20weeks.%20Tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20tonnes%20of%20bombs%20have%20been%20dropped%20into%20the%20most%20densely%20inhabited%20zone%20on%20the%20planet%2C%20fuel%20has%20been%20denied%2C%20and%20water%20and%20medicines%20have%20been%20restricted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20watching%20an%20atrocity%20unparalleled%20compared%20to%20almost%20every%20other%20conflict%20in%20the%20world.%20It%20is%20no%20wonder%20that%20people%20struggle%20to%20understand%20why%20the%20world%20is%20not%20acting%20to%20stop%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20has%20happened%20earlier.%20During%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20similarly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foreignaffairs.com%2Fisrael%2Fghosts-lebanon%3Futm_medium%3Dnewsletters%26utm_source%3Dtwofa%26utm_campaign%3DThe%2520Ghosts%2520of%2520Lebanon%26utm_content%3D20231117%26utm_term%3DFA%2520This%2520Week%2520-%2520112017%5C%22%3Ebrutal%20invasion%20of%20Lebanon%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20then%20US%20President%20Ronald%20Reagan%20called%20up%20the%20Israeli%20Prime%20Minister%20Menachim%20Begin%20%E2%80%93%20former%20head%20of%20the%20Irgun%20terrorist%20militia%20%E2%80%93%20in%201982%20and%20called%20the%20enormous%20damage%20a%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.google.com%2Fnewspapers%3Fid%3Dcr4yAAAAIBAJ%26sjid%3D8O4FAAAAIBAJ%26pg%3D2338%252C4670295%5C%22%3Eholocaust%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D.%20Reagan%20had%20initially%20supported%20the%20operation%20%E2%80%93%20in%20fact%20he%20had%20overridden%20the%20advice%20of%20the%20US%20State%20Department%20to%20meet%20Begin%20%E2%80%93%20but%20his%20use%20of%20such%20a%20term%20to%20an%20Israeli%20PM%20showed%20how%20badly%20it%20had%20all%20gone%2C%20and%20how%20much%20the%20daily%20destruction%20on%20TV%20was%20affecting%20US%20views%20on%20Israel.%20The%20invasion%20led%20to%20the%20destruction%20of%20Lebanon%2C%20a%20violent%20civil%20war%2C%20numerous%20atrocities%2C%20and%20the%20rise%20of%20Hezbollah%20before%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20final%20decision%20to%20withdraw%20%E2%80%93%20many%20years%20later%20%E2%80%93%20in%202000.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20bin%20Laden%20connection%20stems%20from%20another%20war%2C%20one%20far%20more%20publicised%2C%20which%20was%20the%20Balkans%20conflict%20after%20the%20collapse%20of%20Yugoslavia%20in%20the%20early%20%E2%80%9990s%2C%20in%20which%20the%20siege%20of%20Sarajevo%2C%20when%20Serbian%20forces%20ringed%20the%20capital%20of%20Bosnia-Herzegovina%20dropping%20mortar%20shells%20and%20sniping%20at%20will%2C%20lasted%20for%20four%20years%20(April%205%2C%201992%20to%20February%2029%2C%201996).%20Rape%20and%20ethnic%20cleansing%20were%20used%20as%20tools%20of%20war%2C%20and%20the%20murder%20of%20more%20than%207%2C000%20civilians%20in%20the%20UN%20designated%20%E2%80%9Csafe%20zone%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Fevent%2FSrebrenica-massacre%5C%22%3ESrebrenica%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Serbian%20forces%20in%201995%20would%20be%20for%20many%20the%20defining%20moment%20of%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Bosnia's%20Srebrenica%20Genocide%2025%20Years%20On%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fsrebrenica-genocide-25-years-later%5C%22%3EBosnia%E2%80%99s%20Srebrenica%20Genocide%2025%20Years%20On%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20with%20the%20current%20conflict%2C%20many%20did%20not%20understand%20why%20%E2%80%9CNever%20Again%E2%80%9D%20did%20not%20apply.%20Why%20did%20Europe%20dither%3F%20NATO%2C%20primarily%20pushed%20by%20the%20US%20President%20Bill%20Clinton%20%E2%80%93%20launched%20air%20strikes%20after%20the%20Srebrenica%20massacre%20in%201995%20%E2%80%93%20the%20largest%20mass%20murder%20in%20Europe%20after%20World%20War%20II%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20negotiated%20settlement.%20So%20why%20did%20NATO%20wait%20so%20long%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20people%20the%20answer%20was%20simple%3A%20Bosnia-Herzegovina%20was%20majority%20Muslim%20(largely%20pork%20eating%20and%20alcohol%20drinking%20Muslim%2C%20but%20when%20has%20religiosity%20mattered%20in%20ethnic%20conflict%3F).%20Europeans%20and%20the%20US%20were%20hypocrites%2C%20and%20the%20%E2%80%9CWest%E2%80%9D%20would%20not%20save%20Muslims.%20Human%20rights%20had%20no%20meaning%20except%20for%20those%20the%20%E2%80%9CWest%E2%80%9D%20liked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20most%20European%20policymakers%20the%20answer%20was%20different.%20The%20assassination%20of%20Archduke%20Franz%20Ferdinand%20in%20Sarajevo%20in%201914%20set%20off%20a%20chain%20of%20events%20that%20led%20to%20World%20War%20I%2C%20then%20World%20War%20II%2C%20and%20then%20the%20Cold%20War.%20They%20were%20terrified%20of%20getting%20involved%20again.%20Even%20the%20US%2C%20which%20finally%20pushed%20for%20the%20bombings%20and%20was%20instrumental%20in%20the%20end%20of%20the%20war%2C%20was%20initially%20hesitant.%20The%20then%20US%20Secretary%20of%20State%2C%20James%20Baker%20III%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newsweek.com%2Fdog-fight-183518%5C%22%3Efamously%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20a%20dog%20in%20that%20fight.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20for%20the%20young%2C%20for%20those%20not%20of%20Europe%20or%20the%20US%2C%20and%20the%20non-European%20immigrants%20now%20living%20in%20Europe%20and%20the%20US%2C%20this%20was%20neither%20obvious%2C%20nor%20was%20it%20ever%20made%20clear.%20They%20watched%20the%20horror%20play%20out%20every%20day%20on%20their%20screens%2C%20a%20%E2%80%9Cholocaust%E2%80%9D%20as%20Reagan%20would%20have%20said%2C%20and%20did%20not%20understand%20why%20the%20world%20did%20not%20act.%20A%20very%20tiny%20section%20became%20easy%20to%20recruit%20for%20Osama%20bin%20Laden.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20such%20scenes%20are%20repeating.%20For%20the%20US%20and%20Europe%20%E2%80%93%20particularly%20for%20Germany%20%E2%80%93%20the%20backdrop%20is%20the%20Holocaust.%20%E2%80%9CNever%20Again%E2%80%9D%20has%20a%20particular%20resonance%20given%20that%20the%20Hamas%20massacre%20of%20October%207%20%E2%80%93%20primarily%20of%20civilians%20%E2%80%93%20was%20the%20largest%20murder%20of%20Jews%20since%20World%20War%20II.%20But%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%2C%20watching%20the%20horrific%20images%20of%20all%20suffering%20%E2%80%93%20Jewish%2C%20Muslim%2C%20Christian%2C%20whatever%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9CNever%20Again%E2%80%9D%20has%20a%20separate%20meaning.%20It%20is%20not%20about%20Jews%20alone%2C%20but%20about%20humans%20as%20humans.%20They%20will%20inevitably%20conclude%20that%20for%20the%20US%2C%20Europe%2C%20and%20the%20settler%20colonial%20states%20like%20Australia%2C%20Canada%20and%20New%20Zealand%2C%20brown%20lives%2C%20Muslim%20lives%2C%20do%20not%20matter%2C%20and%20the%20suffering%20of%20those%20from%20the%20Global%20South%20has%20no%20meaning.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20there%20will%20be%20inevitably%20those%20that%20traffic%20in%20the%20trauma%20of%20others%20for%20their%20own%20purposes%20who%20will%20use%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20applying%20for%20my%20Masters%20degree%20in%20the%20US%2C%20I%20had%20written%20about%20how%20I%20wanted%20to%20study%20the%20war%20in%20Bosnia-Herzegovina%20and%20how%20it%20had%20been%20seen%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cjust%20war%E2%80%9D%2C%20a%20defensive%20jihad.%20I%20arrived%20in%20the%20US%20in%20August%202001.%20A%20month%20later%2C%20things%20changed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fomair-ahmad%5C%22%3EOmair%20Ahmad%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20an%20author%20and%20journalist.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700390726000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F19160120%2FAerial_photo_of_Mostar_1996.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Flessons-from-bosnia-herzegovinas-forgotten-war%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20people%20struggle%20to%20understand%20the%20scale%20of%20the%20carnage%20in%20Israel-Palestine%2C%20many%20will%20inevitably%20come%20to%20the%20conclusion%20that%20%E2%80%9CWestern%20hypocrisy%E2%80%9D%20is%20the%20answer.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Flessons-from-bosnia-herzegovinas-forgotten-war%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Watch%20%7C%20'Cricket%20World%20Cup%20Final%20Is%20a%20Battle%20of%20Two%20Styles'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F31194438%2FF9nnT1BasAA73q1.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EOut%20of%20the%20Park%20is%C2%A0The%20Wire%E2%80%98s%20Cricket%20World%20Cup%20show%20with%20the%20best%20in%20the%20business%2C%20veteran%20sports%20writer%20and%20journalist%2C%20Sharda%20Ugra.%20She%20pulls%20no%20punches%20and%20firmly%20believes%20in%20hitting%20it%20out%20of%20the%20park.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20321px)%2085vw%2C%20321px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F27140527%2FIMG_2718.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22321%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F27140527%2FIMG_2718.jpg%20800w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F27140527%2FIMG_2718-244x300.jpg%20244w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-682041%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22395%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20eve%20of%20the%20Cricket%20World%20Cup%20final%2C%20Sharda%20Ugra%20interviewed%20Australian%20broadcaster%20Melinda%20Farrell.%20The%20latter%20believes%20that%20the%20final%20will%20be%20a%20clash%20between%20%E2%80%9Ctwo%20different%20styles%20of%20playing%20ODI%20cricket%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20Australia%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cinter%20generation%20confidence%E2%80%9D%20of%20having%20been%20five%20time%20winners%20of%20the%20World%20Cup%20versus%20the%20best%20team%20of%20the%20tournament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20says%20Cricket%20World%20Cups%20should%20not%20become%20%E2%80%9Csmall%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0referring%20to%20the%20fact%20that%2016%20teams%20competed%20in%202015%2C%20but%20with%20only%2010%20in%20the%20current%20edition%2C%20the%20tournament%20feels%20like%20%E2%80%9CChampions%20Trophy%20%2B2%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFarrell%20says%20the%20World%20Cup%20has%20felt%20insular%20as%20broadcasters%20are%20%E2%80%9Cstruggling%20to%20find%20fans%20from%20other%20nations%20in%20the%20crowd%E2%80%9D%20and%20there%20is%20%E2%80%9Cno%20world%20cup%20vibe%E2%80%9D%20in%20any%20of%20the%20cities%20other%20than%20at%20the%20ground.%20She%20says%20fan%20parks%20or%20events%20related%20to%20the%20world%20cup%20have%20not%20been%20planned%2C%20like%20other%20world%20cups%20she%20has%20been%20to.%20The%20broadcaster%20says%20she%20has%20enjoyed%20the%20atmosphere%20in%20non-India%20games%20the%20most.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20praised%20Indian%20fans%20for%20their%20passion%20and%20being%20%E2%80%9Cinvolved%20and%20well%20aware%20of%20the%20history%20and%20cricketers%20from%20other%20countries%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20she%20said%20does%20not%20happen%20in%20most%20other%20places.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FY_y2V0XgB4w%3Fsi%3DZO6FITS2NvG_pAOv%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFarrell%20picked%20out%20Indian%20bowler%20Mohammed%20Shami%20and%20Kiwi%20batsman%20Rachin%20Ravindra%20as%20performers%20of%20the%20event.%20She%20praised%20Ravindra%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Ccross-cultural%20athletic%20wristiness%E2%80%9D%20and%20Shami%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cunfailing%20seam%20position%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20will%20this%20world%20cup%20be%20remembered%20for%3F%20It%20all%20depends%20on%20the%20final%2C%20Farrell%20says.%20Will%20the%20story%20be%20that%20of%20the%20Indian%20juggernaut%20crushing%20the%20rest%20or%20Australia%20re-establishing%20indefatigability.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700389747000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F31194438%2FF9nnT1BasAA73q1.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsport%2Fwatch-cricket-world-cup-final-is-a-battle-of-two-styles%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Will%20the%20story%20be%20that%20of%20the%20Indian%20juggernaut%20crushing%20the%20rest%20or%20Australia%20re-establishing%20indefatigability%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2